PrecisAppointment of Hugh D. Walker, of Edmonton, Alberta, as a governor of the Council of the Canadian Centre for Occupational Health and Safety, being the nominee of the Government of Alberta, to hold office during pleasure for a term of three years, in the place of William Hodson Rozel, who has resigned.
